B4 - Participate in 3 in-class cybersecurity lab activities

Objective
the goal of this activity is to participate in hands-on lab sessions to understand practical cybersecurity concepts

Method
i attended and participated in lab sessions conducted during the unit, where facilitators provided guided cybersecurity activities

Activities
1. Lab activity 1 - we had encrypt one line of text using any ciphers we wanted and had to get other groups to try and decrypt and we had to do the same thing for them
2. Lab activity 2 - in a group we had to figure out the total of our numbers that we wrote without actually sharing it with our group members
3. Lab activity 3 - the third lab was about intrusion detection, we had a pack of cards and the one person kept dealing it on the middle and as a grou p we had to remove the cards that were not considered as normal traffic

Security principle
these lab acitivities demonstrated key cybersecurity principles:
- confidentiality - encryption protects sensitive information from unauthorised access
- privacy preservation - secure computation allows data to be used without revealing it
- integrity - detecting abnormal traffic helps prevent malicious interference
- availability and monitoring - intrusion detection ensures systems remain functional and secure

Evidence
- photos in evidence folder

Reflection
these lab activities helped me understand cybersecurity concepts in a practical and interactive way. the encryption task showed how data can be protected, while the secure computation acitvity demonstrated privacy-preserving techniques. the intrusion detection simulation made it clear how systems monitor and filter abnormal behaviour. overall, these activities improved my understanding of how cybersecurity principles are applied in real-world scenarios.
